Great quality, another present for my mom. She wasn't too into the show itself, she felt they could have done better, but it was fun to watch.

This series is so funny but I don't like that they cut it short while filming. It seems like there could be a continuation which would be amazing but I don't expect it anytime in the future. I loved this series when I first watched it and I am happy that I bought it. The subtitles are a bit off with tenses and I vs I'll vs I'd. If you get passed the subtitles it's not a bad copy at all.

Thousands of people dream to be k-pop idols and try out for auditions, but only a few will make the cut. This is a great drama about the challenges and difficulties of a group of guys (and a girl undercover as a boy) following their dreams in becoming a group of k-pop stars and competing against another already popular k-pop group. Also, having a girl pulling a gender bender and being thrown in with a group of guys there is bound to be some romance and laugh out loud comedy. The music in this drama is amazing and fits the show perfectly.

It has good English subtitles.
As the title says, English subtitle was easier to understand rather than any other Korean TV dramas I bought in the past.
